      "writtenOn": "2018-02-09T18:42:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The problem is due to the following:\n\n- During build we generate executable for the HOST (linux-x86_64) to produce more source for TARGET (windows_x86)\n- libc++.so for clang is ELF64, we don\u0027t have ELF32 version\n- Due to some bugs in our build scripts the bitness of TARGET and HOST must match. \n\nThe last part is the problem. Previously our toolchain could create a 32 bit executable on linux. Now we cannot. \n\nSo for now we just disable it, and re-introduce it later when we are ready to fix the build scripts.",
